<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" Description="Contains all calibrations for GIS-618 SystemState specifications">
  <CalDefFileVersion>14</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>11APR14</Date>
    <Description>Reviewed for compliance to CalDef Guidelines. - Jon G</Description>
    <Author>John Edens</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>2/27/2015</Date>
    <Description>Updated to add missing usages on two cals (UPDATE_AVAILABLE_LOCAL_INFOTAINMENT_TIMEOUT and MASTER_OFFMODE_ACTIVE_TIMEOUT) that didn't have usages </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>01JUN15</Date>
    <Description>Set CRITICAL_STATE_OF_CHARGE_IGNORE default TRUE.</Description>
    <Author>John Edens</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>June 20, 2016</Date>
    <Description>Added calibrations needed for GIS-618-880 Suspend To RAM functionality:  SUSPEND_TO_RAM_ENABLE, MAXIMUM_SUSPEND_TIME, MAXIMUM_RESUME_TIME.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>06/22/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added calibration for GIS-618-490 to add NEW cal for DISABLED_OFFMODE_TIMEOUT</Description>
    <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef updated the default value of  the VIN_RELEARN_EN calibration from a value of False to True, to allow for VIN relearn once MEC is set to zero since this capability is needed by the GM Manufacturing Plants.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>10/28/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added the following four calibrations from GIS-651: 1) GIS-618-492 RSI_ANIMATION_IGNORE ~MY19; 2) GIS-618-494 CLUSTER_ANIMATION_IGNORE ~MY19; 3) GIS-618-496 RSI_HMIREADY_IGNORE ~MY19; 4) GIS-618-498 CLUSTER_HMIREADY IGNORE ~MY19 </Description>
    <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>9/20/2017</Date>
    <Description>For CR# 1476934, within the GIS618_SystemState.caldef: Added the following eight new calibrations: 1.) OFFMODE_ACTIVE_TIMEOUT, 2.) REMOTE_REFLASH_PROGRAMMING_COMPLETE_TIMEOUT, 3.) POWERMODE_FAILURE_TIMEOUT, 4.) POWERMODE_FAILURE_TIMEOUT, 5.) SUSPEND_PREPARATION_TIMEOUT, 6.) SUSPEND_TIME, 7.) RESUME_FAULT_TIMEOUT, and  8.) MAXIMUM_FLUSH_FAULT_TIME introduced in GIS-618 version 2.4. Also, made a Cal Description Only Update for additional clarity for the following Cals: 1.) SUSPEND_TO_RAM_ENABLE and 2.) MAXIMUM_SUSPEND_TIME.</Description>
    <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS618_SystemState.caldef file, added GEM usage to all of the calibrations within this caldef, except for the following calibrations within this caldef file: 1.) SUSPEND_PREPARATION_TIMEOUT,  2.) SUSPEND_TIME, 3.) RESUME_FAULT_TIMEOUT, 4.) MAXIMUM_FLUSH_FAULT_TIME, 5.) MAXIMUM_SUSPEND_TIME, 6.) SUSPEND_TO_RAM_ENABLE, and 7.) MAXIMUM_RESUME_TIME.. Note, did not add GEM usage for these seven calibrations since these seven calibraions did not fall within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>12/212017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS618_SystemState.caldef added a new calibration called SHUTDOWN_DELAY_TIMEOUT calibration to address PRTS#: 28629 for MY20 and beyond.  Per CR 1053172, revised UPDATE_AVAILABLE_LOCAL_INFOTAINMENT_TIMEOUT default.</Description>
    <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>09/24/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#1535805, within GIS618_SystemState.caldef the default value of INFOTAINMENT_ACTIVITY_TIMEOUT has been changed from 8 to 30 seconds.</Description>
    <Author>Younus A. Syed</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>3-17-2021</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#2901735 made the following updates within the GIS618_SystemState.caldef file: Added the following 8 new cals:  FLUSH_LIMIT_TIME, STR_MIN_TEMP_THRESHOLD, STR_MODE_SOC_MIN_THRESHOLD_1, STR_MODE_SOC_MIN_THRESHOLD_2, STR_MODE_SOC_MIN_THRESHOLD_3, MAX_SUSPEND_TIME_1, MAX_SUSPEND_TIME_2, MAX_SUSPEND_TIME_3</Description>
    <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="Timeout value used to delay transitioning of System State to Sleep to ensure that the external Amplifier completes playing of &#x201c;Shutdown Animation&#x201d; audio cue before CSM/Low Radio/GEM enters Sleep State" Name="SHUTDOWN_DELAY_TIMEOUT" References="GIS-618-537" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_ofo5EOAtEeeOY4lmtLFarg</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>12/13/2017</Date>
      <Description>Initial release </Description>
      <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>15</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>120</MaxValue>
      <Units>seconds</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration shall define the Timeout value used to force an exit from HMIInactive.Inactive Substate to Sleep State to ensure that the CSM/Low Radio does not remain awake when an event to trigger the transition to the OffModeActive Substate does not occur." Name="OFFMODE_ACTIVE_TIMEOUT" References="GIS-618-525" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_pExQQJ8PEeeKqKPvPjizjg</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>9/20/2017</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release</Description>
      <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>30</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>120</MaxValue>
      <Units>seconds</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="This calibration shall define the Timeout value used to force an exit from RemoteReflashProgramming.RemoteReflashProgrammingComplete substate" Name="REMOTE_REFLASH_PROGRAMMING_COMPLETE_TIMEOUT" References="GIS-618-530" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
