  <CalDefinition Description="As part of the Component-Level TheftLock and VIN Learning Logic, the internal ModuleTheftLockedFlag within a component may only be cleared upon receipt of the evClearVINCPID event.  This event is generated in response to the VIN clearing CPID $FE that is sent to the CSM/Low Radio from a service tool.  Note that clearing back to a NoVIN condition is guarded by the CSM/Low Radio&#x2019;s Internal Manufacturing Enable Counter or MEC as well as a VIN_RELEARN_EN calibration that is used to bypass VIN learning altogether in particular regions where Theftlock is not required but the same end model part number is used for a component. " Name="VIN_RELEARN_EN" References="GIS-618-1810" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_AUJ78LnPEeONt_iAU7Ji9A</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>10/24/2016</Date>
      <Description>Updated the default value of  the VIN_RELEARN_EN calibration from a value of False to True, to allow for VIN relearn once MEC is set to zero since this capability is needed by the GM Manufacturing Plants.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated vehicle architectural usage to add GEM usage for this calibration because it fell within the current criteria of calibrations that require GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Master switch to enable or disable Suspend to RAM functionality.  Default value must always be False to reduce probability of mis-calibration.This calibration shall allow the CSM to enable or disable Suspend-To-RAM functionality. When this calibration is enabled (i.e. set to a value equal to TRUE), the CSM shall enable the Suspend-To-RAM feature. When this calibration is disabled (i.e. set to a value equal to FALSE), the CSM shall disable the Suspend-To-RAM feature." Name="SUSPEND_TO_RAM_ENABLE" References="GIS-618-510" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_koSLcDb7EeanKtszDwv8Ww</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>June 20, 2016</Date>
      <Description>Inital release of this calibration</Description>
      <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>9/20/2017</Date>
      <Description>Cal Description Only Update for additional clarity</Description>
      <Author>Younus Syed</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Maximum Suspend time for Suspend To RAM feature.  Maximum has been set to 68 hours which simplifies implementation of timer within CSM VIP processor architecture. This calibration shall define the maximum length of time in suspended mode before a full shutdown must be performed in order to preserve vehicle battery capacity. Upon timeout VIP will resume SOC to start Flush-from-Suspend procedure." Name="MAXIMUM_SUSPEND_TIME" References="GIS-618-515" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_yTW0UDb7EeanKtszDwv8Ww</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
